{
  "text": "Migratory pulmonary cDCs consist of CD11b \u00fe and CD103 \u00fe DC subsets. [CITATION_1] CD103 \u00fe DCs are specialized to phagocytize apoptotic cells and cross present exogenous antigen on MHCI molecules; however, both subsets can present antigen to CD4 \u00fe T cells. [CITATION_2] Analysis of CD11b \u00fe and CD103 \u00fe cDC subsets ( Figure 3e ) showed an increased percentage of the AF647-ova \u00fe cDCs in AF647-ova \u00fe beryllium-treated mice of the CD11b \u00fe subset compared with mice treated with AF647-ova alone. However, the total numbers of both AF647-ova \u00fe",
